# Try...Catch ðŸ¥…

Don't let your app crash! Catch errors.

```javascript
try {
  // Code that might fail
  let x = y + 1; // y is not defined
} catch (error) {
  // Code that runs if error occurs
  console.log("An error occurred: " + error.message);
}
```

## Finally
Runs regardless of result (cleanup).
```javascript
finally {
  console.log("Done");
}
```

# Throwing Errors âš¾

You can manually trigger errors.

```javascript
function checkAge(age) {
  if (age < 18) {
    throw new Error("Access Denied: Too young");
  }
  return "Access Granted";
}

try {
  checkAge(15);
} catch (e) {
  console.error(e.message);
}
```
